                    <p>My son Zach just finished a high school paper on the history of Italian food and he says that carbonara doesn't mean coal miner it means charcoal maker. It seems that when the men left for the woods to make charcoal they took with them the ingredients (cheese, egg, garlic) and cooked it themselves. Zach has a recipe for Linguine Carbonara that uses Cheez Whiz instead of parmesan and tabasco instead of garlic and it is pretty good. If he wasn't so short he could be a TV chef one day!</p>
